Team Delta defeated Rivers 8-2 yesterday in the opening match of the maiden Victor Chukwudumebi Achakpo 2022 National Division 1 Baseball and Softball championships in Asaba. Lagos State baseball team also started well by beating Kwara State 7-6 in a close contest while Team Delta also recorded victory in their second baseball game against Niger, which ended 15-3. In the Softball event, Delta also started on victory note, beating Kwara 8-0. 		 			Feyenoord gets Genk’s transfer deadline for Dessers		 		 		 			Makinde to commission building donated to IGC		 		 		 			Revealed: How El Rufai turned around Kaduna cricket		 		 The competition which will end tomorrow, is being attended by Baseball Division 1 teams from Delta, Kwara, Lagos, Ekiti and Niger State, while Division 1 teams from Delta, Rivers, Kwara and Lagos will fight in the Softball event with over N1million cash prizes up for grab. The competition is holding at the St. Patrick’s College (SPC), Asaba. Meanwhile, Rivers baseball team will face Niger and Lagos against Ekiti this morning while afternoon games will see Lagos softball team do battle with Delta, while Kwara face Rivers. The semifinal will hold on later today, while the third place match and final game hold on April 24.